    • Field Detail

      • routeName

        public java.lang.String routeName
        The name of the route. Note: This cannot contain whitespace characters (ie spaces, tabs, or new lines), as its used in a url.

      • color

        public int color
        The color of the route. This is optional, as there is a high chance that the route does not have one.

        This is an int instead of a Color object because for whatever reason android stores its colors as ints.

      • stops

        public Stop[] stops
        The array of stops for this route. This may be empty / null if the route has not been initialized, and the stops haven't been loaded.

      • buses

        public Bus[] buses
        The array of buses that correspond to this route.

      • polyLineCoordinates

        public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng[] polyLineCoordinates
        The array of LatLng coordinates that will be used to create the polyline (if enabled). This should be initialized with an array of length 0.

    • Method Detail

      • generateRoutes

        public static Route[] generateRoutes(org.json.JSONObject masterSchedule)
        Dynamically generates the routes that are used by parsing the master schedule. This may return an empty route array if there was an issue parsing the data, or if there were no routes to parse based off the master schedule.
        Parameters:
        masterSchedule - The master schedule JSONObject from teh RouteMatch server
        Returns:
        An array of routes that can be tracked.

      • enableRoutes

        public static Route[] enableRoutes(java.lang.String routeName,
                                   Route[] oldRoutes)
        Enabled a route by route name, and returns a new array of enabled routes including the previously enabled routes.
        Parameters:
        routeName - The new route to enable (by route name).
        oldRoutes - The array of old routes that were previously enabled. If there were no previously enabled routes then this must be an array of size 0.
        Returns:
        The array of routes that are now being tracked.

      • disableRoute

        public static Route[] disableRoute(java.lang.String routeName,
                                   Route[] oldRoutes)
        Disables a route by name, and removes all elements of that route from the map (except stops).
        Parameters:
        routeName - The route the be disabled by name.
        oldRoutes - The array of old, though currently enabled routes.
        Returns:
        The array of routes still to be tracked, with the omission of the route that was to be removed. If there are no more routes that are to be enabled, then an array of size 0 will be returned.

      • loadStops

        public Stop[] loadStops(RouteMatch routeMatch)
        Loads the stops from the provided url. If there was an error parsing the JSON data for the stop object, then this will return what stops it had parsed successfully up until that point. As a result, the Stop array returned may be smaller than expected, or have a length of 0.
        Parameters:
        routeMatch - The route match instance (for pulling from the RouteMatch server).
        Returns:
        The array of stops that were loaded.
